                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 Refugee Settlement Commission/18:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-03-31T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1923—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. See our telegram for Haskell quoting message from Payne.<note n="12"
                        xml:id="d226fn12">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0456" n="332" xml:id="pg_332"/>
                <p>In your discretion you may transmit to the Greek authorities the substance of the
                    memorandum regarding relief work in the Near East presented to the British,
                    French, and Italian Ambassadors in Washington today. The text of this memorandum
                    is being telegraphed to you through our Embassy in Paris.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
